Synthesis anarchism, synthesist anarchism, synthesism or synthesis Synthesis anarchism, also known as synthesist anarchism or simply synthesism, is a philosophical approach that seeks to combine various anarchist schools of thought in order to create a more comprehensive and adaptable theory of social organization and resistance. This approach is characterized by its emphasis on unity, cooperation, and the integration of diverse strategies and ideas to strengthen the anarchist movement. It recognizes the value of anarchist principles such as direct action, horizontal organization, and voluntary association, while also acknowledging the importance of flexibility and adaptability in the face of changing social conditions. By embracing a synthesis of different perspectives, synthesis anarchism aims to create a more inclusive and effective movement that can respond to the complexities of the modern world.
